1
00:01:36,063 --> 00:01:39,316
General, the princess's convoy
has entered our realm.

2
00:01:40,025 --> 00:01:41,109
Prepare to receive them.

3
00:01:41,193 --> 00:01:42,569
Prepare to receive them!

4
00:01:42,735 --> 00:01:43,987
Prepare to receive them!

5
00:02:27,277 --> 00:02:32,575
General Meng Yi of Qin
welcomes Your Highness.

6
00:02:33,868 --> 00:02:36,829
May it please Her Highness.

7
00:02:46,296 --> 00:02:48,006
His Imperial Majesty decrees...

8
00:02:53,469 --> 00:02:57,515
that Princess Ok Soo
shall be Concubine Li of Qin,

9
00:02:57,932 --> 00:03:00,768
for our nations' mutual
peace and harmony.

10
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,687
This is what Princess Ok Soo
was ordered to do.

11
00:03:32,381 --> 00:03:35,509
My orders are to bring back
Princess Ok Soo.

12
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,890
Whoever interferes shall die!

13
00:03:42,308 --> 00:03:44,560
Her Royal Highness
is now Concubine Li of Qin.

14
00:03:44,935 --> 00:03:47,979
Whoever dares to go against this order
is an enemy of our state!

15
00:03:50,774 --> 00:03:54,694
They leave us no alternative.

16
00:03:55,903 --> 00:03:57,029
Prepare to attack.

17
00:04:01,742 --> 00:04:02,910
Ready defenses.

18
00:04:03,118 --> 00:04:03,994
Ready defenses!

19
00:04:37,109 --> 00:04:39,362
Hurry! Protect the Princess!

20
00:04:46,409 --> 00:04:47,702
Hurry! Get away from this place!

21
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:23,933
Please come back with me.

22
00:07:24,934 --> 00:07:26,561
You are already my betrothed.

23
00:07:28,438 --> 00:07:30,189
I cannot go back with you.

24
00:07:31,941 --> 00:07:34,527
I cannot abide you
marrying the moribund emperor.

25
00:07:37,488 --> 00:07:39,448
It's a surrender
of our sovereignty to Qin!

26
00:07:40,449 --> 00:07:41,867
I was forced into this decision.

27
00:07:42,368 --> 00:07:43,286
Please understand.

28
00:07:44,495 --> 00:07:47,706
You are a general!
How can you taint my honor?

29
00:08:19,195 --> 00:08:20,071
Come!

30
00:08:21,530 --> 00:08:23,615
My mission is to protect the princess.

31
00:08:28,870 --> 00:08:30,997
Draw your sword.
Let's both fulfill

32
00:08:31,832 --> 00:08:32,708
our missions.

33
00:09:32,973 --> 00:09:34,516
Protect the princess.

34
00:09:42,106 --> 00:09:43,065
Save her!

35
00:09:46,235 --> 00:09:47,111
Run!

36
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:55,661
Your Highness!

37
00:10:39,411 --> 00:10:42,163
28 Feb 2005

38
00:10:42,538 --> 00:10:46,209
I have had the same dream
for months now.

39
00:10:46,835 --> 00:10:50,171
This time, I'm an ancient general

40
00:10:52,423 --> 00:10:53,841
leading a vast army...

41
00:10:56,134 --> 00:10:57,511
to rescue...

42
00:10:58,596 --> 00:11:00,138
some sort of princess.

43
00:11:01,974 --> 00:11:03,892
I fell off a cliff...

44
00:11:09,397 --> 00:11:11,524
Hello? William?

45
00:11:11,774 --> 00:11:14,736
You're back in Hong Kong?
Great! Come on over!

46
00:11:20,783 --> 00:11:24,495
Talk about being at sea!

47
00:11:25,037 --> 00:11:26,455
Why are you living on a barge?

48
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:28,749
The research budget
was cut in half last year.

49
00:11:28,999 --> 00:11:32,961
With the project unfinished,
I had to sell the flat.

50
00:11:33,587 --> 00:11:35,506
So, I moved here with my study.

51
00:11:36,715 --> 00:11:39,009
It's not so bad!
Pretty roomy here.

52
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:41,385
So why are you back suddenly?

53
00:11:41,469 --> 00:11:42,804
You didn't like the United States?

54
00:11:42,929 --> 00:11:45,181
I came to solve your financial problems.

55
00:11:50,270 --> 00:11:52,062
I want you to do something for me.

56
00:11:53,523 --> 00:11:55,983
<i>Hi, William! This must be Dr. Chan.</i>

57
00:11:56,441 --> 00:11:58,360
Just call me Jack.

58
00:11:59,278 --> 00:12:02,281
<i>I'm Maggie. Welcome to our
Anti-Gravity Research Project.</i>

59
00:12:03,740 --> 00:12:06,785
- Anti-Gravity?
- This is my lab. Check it out.

60
00:12:08,620 --> 00:12:11,080
<i>Let's ask Dr. Smith
to give a little demonstration.</i>

61
00:12:29,932 --> 00:12:32,267
<i>These are very expensive experiments.</i>

62
00:12:32,643 --> 00:12:36,438
<i>Quite impractical,
and unusable on living subjects</i>

63
00:12:37,522 --> 00:12:40,733
<i>as no living creature
can survive such speed.</i>

64
00:12:45,155 --> 00:12:47,990
I don't understand.
You're a physicist,

65
00:12:48,241 --> 00:12:49,826
I'm an archaeologist.
How can I help you?

66
00:12:51,285 --> 00:12:54,038
I'm seeking a breakthrough
in the field of mysterious phenomena.

67
00:12:55,414 --> 00:12:57,416
Remember that paper you wrote?

68
00:12:58,334 --> 00:13:01,837
Over 2,000 years ago,
there was a tiny kingdom south of Dasar

69
00:13:02,338 --> 00:13:04,881
whose king became immortal after death.

70
00:13:05,090 --> 00:13:06,717
His coffin floated in mid-air.

71
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:09,553
Your paper inspired me.

72
00:13:10,637 --> 00:13:12,055
It's just a myth.

73
00:13:12,430 --> 00:13:14,556
I can even lend you comic books
about this.

74
00:13:14,641 --> 00:13:17,727
Lots of things are called myths
prior to empirical verification.

75
00:13:20,730 --> 00:13:22,940
Wireless telephony
was a myth 150 years ago.

76
00:13:23,358 --> 00:13:26,818
So was the airplane,
and landing on the moon!

77
00:13:26,902 --> 00:13:28,779
Even 50 years ago,

78
00:13:28,863 --> 00:13:31,115
computer and digital technology
were a myth.

79
00:13:31,741 --> 00:13:34,409
Many people are competing
to develop this technology.

80
00:13:34,827 --> 00:13:36,411
If I succeed,

81
00:13:36,495 --> 00:13:38,163
I'll change human history.

82
00:13:38,705 --> 00:13:40,665
This technology could be vital
to our lives,

83
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:45,295
to surface and air transportation,
even inter-galactic travel!

84
00:13:48,715 --> 00:13:51,342
I know you've always wanted
to do something great.

85
00:13:52,301 --> 00:13:54,971
No one's ever entered
this ancient tomb before.

86
00:13:55,346 --> 00:13:57,765
But my work is archaeology,
and I have my ethic.

87
00:13:58,682 --> 00:14:00,684
I do research, not raid tombs.

88
00:14:08,441 --> 00:14:09,484
You still can't forget

89
00:14:10,152 --> 00:14:11,904
that incident, after all these years?

90
00:14:12,695 --> 00:14:15,157
There are things you never forget.

91
00:14:21,204 --> 00:14:22,705
We haven't played in ages.

92
00:14:23,540 --> 00:14:24,707
How's your game?

93
00:14:27,459 --> 00:14:28,711
Jack!

94
00:14:34,466 --> 00:14:35,592
Don't you practice anymore?

95
00:14:35,759 --> 00:14:38,345
Of course I do, but I just
never shot from this angle before.

96
00:14:38,762 --> 00:14:41,348
- So why shoot?
- Because you passed it to me.

97
00:14:41,515 --> 00:14:42,724
Don't worry about it.
Come on.

98
00:14:43,392 --> 00:14:46,520
That Maggie is your girlfriend?

99
00:14:46,770 --> 00:14:50,690
No. She represents my sponsor.
By the way, what happened to Monica?

100
00:14:51,232 --> 00:14:53,026
Monica? Forget her.

101
00:14:53,318 --> 00:14:55,903
I've been dreaming about a princess.

102
00:14:56,404 --> 00:14:58,323
Her name's Ok Soo.

103
00:14:58,698 --> 00:15:00,741
I called out her name in my sleep.

104
00:15:01,492 --> 00:15:02,827
How do you think Monica took it?

105
00:15:04,369 --> 00:15:05,788
Now, back to business.

106
00:15:06,413 --> 00:15:08,874
Jack, you've never been
a stickler for rules.

107
00:15:09,166 --> 00:15:11,126
You've always trusted your instincts.

108
00:15:11,501 --> 00:15:15,047
Instincts helped you
unravel the Dead Sea Scrolls forgery...

109
00:15:15,714 --> 00:15:16,965
Jack, hey...

110
00:15:17,299 --> 00:15:18,550
Jack!

111
00:15:23,638 --> 00:15:24,513
Jack!

112
00:15:25,389 --> 00:15:26,975
Do as your instincts tell you.

113
00:15:27,558 --> 00:15:29,310
I want to prove it's not a myth,

114
00:15:30,353 --> 00:15:31,437
but something real.

115
00:15:40,863 --> 00:15:41,822
You're my best friend.

116
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,659
I trust you won't let me
face danger alone.

117
00:15:47,327 --> 00:15:48,954
Ever tried hitting a golf shot like this?

118
00:16:26,156 --> 00:16:27,032
Jack!

119
00:16:27,865 --> 00:16:30,326
- What's with you?
- I think I've got heat stroke.

120
00:16:30,701 --> 00:16:32,036
Almost there. Come on!

121
00:16:32,370 --> 00:16:33,996
Don't lie to me now.

122
00:16:35,164 --> 00:16:36,916
You should exercise more regularly.

123
00:16:37,332 --> 00:16:39,794
I do! Three hours of golf each day,

124
00:16:40,127 --> 00:16:41,754
two hours of tennis...

125
00:16:41,879 --> 00:16:43,964
And another dozen hours a day
playing video games.

126
00:16:44,048 --> 00:16:45,424
You'll go blind in no time.

127
00:16:45,966 --> 00:16:47,926
If you're so fit, why don't you carry me?

128
00:16:48,052 --> 00:16:49,469
You can walk. Hurry Up.

129
00:16:49,928 --> 00:16:51,471
We won't get in if we're late!

130
00:16:59,437 --> 00:17:02,190
Jack, that's the holy man who can fly?

131
00:17:02,648 --> 00:17:04,733
Yes. Let's go over there.

132
00:17:09,071 --> 00:17:10,614
He really can fly...

133
00:17:20,623 --> 00:17:22,292
Get up. Follow me.

134
00:17:24,252 --> 00:17:26,129
Hey, up, up.

135
00:17:28,381 --> 00:17:29,757
- Hurry.
- Give me a hand.

136
00:17:29,841 --> 00:17:31,133
Grab hold of my leg!

137
00:17:34,345 --> 00:17:36,347
- You've got strong legs.
- Let go!

138
00:17:38,975 --> 00:17:40,684
Wow! Nice stone carvings!

139
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:43,062
You have no idea
how many stories they tell.

140
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:46,022
I didn't come this far
on my last expedition.

141
00:18:05,416 --> 00:18:06,501
Jack!

142
00:18:18,678 --> 00:18:20,096
The stone coffin's floating here.

143
00:18:20,180 --> 00:18:23,100
- Zoom in and see if it's suspended.
- I'm working on it already.

144
00:18:25,227 --> 00:18:26,144
Jack,

145
00:18:26,978 --> 00:18:29,439
there's a sword beside the coffin.

146
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:32,024
I can see it.

147
00:18:32,108 --> 00:18:35,486
I think the inscription
records his deeds.

148
00:18:37,238 --> 00:18:39,532
"Mission to Qin"?

149
00:18:40,158 --> 00:18:43,786
"This prince once brought treasures
and women to Qin.

150
00:18:43,994 --> 00:18:48,040
The Qin Emperor gifted him
one of his concubines,

151
00:18:48,541 --> 00:18:53,211
but he picked the emperor's favorite.

152
00:18:53,378 --> 00:18:56,965
The emperor reneged
and gave him her painting instead,

153
00:18:57,465 --> 00:19:01,386
as well as the Qin Star Gem in apology.

154
00:19:01,511 --> 00:19:06,516
The prince even fought against
Qin's greatest warrior,

155
00:19:07,475 --> 00:19:09,101
exchanging swords with him."

156
00:19:18,069 --> 00:19:19,528
- Hey! Don't!
- What?

157
00:19:30,664 --> 00:19:31,581
Jack!

158
00:19:32,916 --> 00:19:35,001
- Are you all right?
- What did you just move?

159
00:19:37,253 --> 00:19:38,754
I've never seen stones like these.

160
00:19:39,172 --> 00:19:40,840
I want some for research.

161
00:19:41,174 --> 00:19:42,633
I told you not to steal anything!

162
00:19:43,384 --> 00:19:45,052
I was going to return it afterwards.

163
00:19:45,886 --> 00:19:47,304
It almost cost me my life!

164
00:19:47,763 --> 00:19:51,641
How come the coffin fell
as soon as I pulled it out?

165
00:20:18,417 --> 00:20:19,627
His Majesty requested me

166
00:20:19,752 --> 00:20:23,005
to paint a portrait of Concubine Li
as a gift to the Prince of Dasar.

167
00:20:23,422 --> 00:20:26,258
If she won't smile, how can I paint?

168
00:20:28,468 --> 00:20:30,846
I've not seen her smile since she arrived.

169
00:20:33,265 --> 00:20:34,932
General Meng!

170
00:20:56,537 --> 00:20:57,871
Excellent!

171
00:20:58,622 --> 00:21:00,916
That's the smile!

172
00:21:05,211 --> 00:21:06,587
Jack!

173
00:21:07,213 --> 00:21:10,508
Stop dreaming!
I hear footsteps!

174
00:21:14,762 --> 00:21:17,848
- Quick! Lift it up!
- Why don't you ask them to help?

175
00:21:37,701 --> 00:21:38,952
Jack!

176
00:21:39,077 --> 00:21:40,369
Help me!

177
00:21:51,214 --> 00:21:52,756
Come on! Let go!

178
00:22:35,714 --> 00:22:36,715
Hey.

179
00:23:04,992 --> 00:23:06,326
Who are you?

180
00:23:06,618 --> 00:23:08,537
Why come and desecrate our sacred temple?

181
00:23:08,828 --> 00:23:10,289
What do you gain by this?

182
00:23:17,128 --> 00:23:19,463
I just came in to look for something,

183
00:23:19,881 --> 00:23:21,966
I didn't mean to wreck the coffin.

184
00:23:22,508 --> 00:23:24,052
It was an accident.

185
00:23:25,303 --> 00:23:26,470
Sorry.

186
00:23:33,769 --> 00:23:35,688
Are you all right?

187
00:23:36,104 --> 00:23:37,564
I was apologizing.

188
00:23:38,065 --> 00:23:40,067
How was I to know?
I was trying to help.

189
00:23:40,233 --> 00:23:41,609
- Let's go.
- Wait.

190
00:23:41,859 --> 00:23:43,320
I told you not to steal.

191
00:23:44,279 --> 00:23:45,572
It's for protection.

192
00:23:48,325 --> 00:23:49,617
Let's go, Jack!

193
00:23:50,493 --> 00:23:52,579
- I took the painting for you as well.
- What?

194
00:24:00,461 --> 00:24:01,337
Run.

195
00:24:08,635 --> 00:24:10,136
- Jack!
- Wait.

196
00:24:23,691 --> 00:24:24,817
Get up. Let's go.

197
00:24:45,003 --> 00:24:46,170
Jack!

198
00:24:46,380 --> 00:24:47,630
Didn't you say you had backup?

199
00:24:47,714 --> 00:24:49,465
All I see are monkeys!

200
00:24:55,138 --> 00:24:56,180
You get on board first.

201
00:25:02,895 --> 00:25:03,896
Jack!

202
00:25:17,450 --> 00:25:19,327
It is too dangerous,
we have to leave now!

203
00:25:20,412 --> 00:25:21,913
Come on! Jack!
Fly a bit lower!

204
00:25:22,038 --> 00:25:24,206
No! We are hit! Let's go!

205
00:25:25,833 --> 00:25:27,919
Jack! Jack!

206
00:25:30,129 --> 00:25:31,130
Jack!

207
00:26:22,804 --> 00:26:23,930
Thank God!

208
00:26:39,945 --> 00:26:40,946
Concubine Li!

209
00:26:44,282 --> 00:26:45,242
Concubine Li!

210
00:27:31,827 --> 00:27:34,622
Your Highness,
forgive my lapse in your protection.

211
00:27:58,812 --> 00:28:00,479
Halt!
Lay down your sword!

212
00:28:00,772 --> 00:28:01,815
or I'll kill her!

213
00:28:10,198 --> 00:28:11,073
Don't!

214
00:28:12,325 --> 00:28:15,118
If only one can live,
I'd rather it be you.

215
00:28:23,085 --> 00:28:24,252
Drop it!

216
00:28:39,016 --> 00:28:40,142
General!

217
00:28:53,363 --> 00:28:55,574
- General Meng Yi!
- Don't help me.

218
00:28:56,658 --> 00:28:58,159
I'm beneath your station.

219
00:29:00,745 --> 00:29:03,289
Why do you
risk your life for me?

220
00:29:05,333 --> 00:29:07,960
A blade is forged
to drink the blood of enemies.

221
00:29:08,586 --> 00:29:11,171
I am like a blade,
destined to fight for His Majesty,

222
00:29:11,714 --> 00:29:13,257
and die for my country.

223
00:29:14,174 --> 00:29:17,052
You are now Concubine Li of Qin.
Protecting you is my duty.

224
00:29:17,887 --> 00:29:19,554
Your Highness has suffered a fright.

225
00:29:21,931 --> 00:29:23,600
With you beside me,

226
00:29:24,101 --> 00:29:25,519
I'm not afraid of anything.

227
00:29:31,650 --> 00:29:34,193
We cannot stay here.
We must leave quickly.

228
00:40:03,331 --> 00:40:04,207
Meng Yi...

229
00:40:06,209 --> 00:40:07,710
General Meng Yi!

230
00:40:16,426 --> 00:40:18,720
General, come in.

231
00:40:23,517 --> 00:40:24,393
Meng Yi...

232
00:40:35,194 --> 00:40:37,280
Meng Yi? General Meng Yi?

233
00:40:44,119 --> 00:40:47,831
You promised to protect me.
You can't die!

234
00:41:13,981 --> 00:41:15,191
Meng Yi?

235
00:41:17,151 --> 00:41:18,694
Meng Yi? Meng Yi...

236
00:41:28,912 --> 00:41:30,246
I have nothing

237
00:41:30,747 --> 00:41:32,082
left in this world.

238
00:41:33,374 --> 00:41:34,792
Not even a relative.

239
00:42:05,530 --> 00:42:06,906
Please don't abandon me!

240
00:42:08,992 --> 00:42:11,494
I have nothing left but you.

241
00:42:13,621 --> 00:42:15,081
Please don't leave me alone!

242
00:43:10,383 --> 00:43:11,717
General Meng Yi.

243
00:43:12,093 --> 00:43:13,469
Over here, quickly.

244
00:43:21,936 --> 00:43:24,730
This is the first time
I've felt so free.

245
00:43:25,981 --> 00:43:27,732
No courtly rites and regulations.

246
00:43:29,193 --> 00:43:30,319
What a beautiful feeling.

247
00:43:31,278 --> 00:43:33,447
This is the first time
I've seen Your Highness smile.

248
00:43:36,240 --> 00:43:38,952
- Why don't you look at me?
- Your humble servant does not dare.

249
00:43:42,205 --> 00:43:43,497
Don't say such things.

250
00:43:43,832 --> 00:43:45,208
Don't take away this feeling.

251
00:43:46,667 --> 00:43:48,669
I'll stop calling you general.

252
00:43:49,837 --> 00:43:51,255
How's that, Meng Yi?

253
00:44:02,182 --> 00:44:04,517
I want to dance.
Shall I dance for you?

254
00:44:05,685 --> 00:44:07,062
No, Your Highness. You mustn't.

255
00:44:07,187 --> 00:44:09,397
In this world, only the emperor
himself may watch.

256
00:44:10,315 --> 00:44:11,399
This is a dance

257
00:44:11,691 --> 00:44:13,025
for you alone.

258
00:45:44,196 --> 00:45:45,405
Please, Your Highness.

259
00:46:13,890 --> 00:46:15,391
We have reached the Great Wall.

260
00:46:16,684 --> 00:46:18,269
This is entirely our realm.

261
00:46:19,312 --> 00:46:22,315
Our capital, Xianyang
is just over the hill.

262
00:46:23,566 --> 00:46:26,402
You are now safe, Concubine Li.

263
00:46:27,778 --> 00:46:30,740
I have finally
accomplished my mission.

264
00:46:33,743 --> 00:46:34,743
No!

265
00:46:35,327 --> 00:46:36,703
I don't want to go to Xianyang.

266
00:46:38,122 --> 00:46:40,499
Take me away.
Take me anywhere.

267
00:46:40,999 --> 00:46:42,376
I only want to be with you.

268
00:46:44,002 --> 00:46:45,712
I don't want to marry the emperor.

269
00:47:04,730 --> 00:47:07,566
Why did we struggle to stay alive,

270
00:47:09,735 --> 00:47:12,029
just to become slaves to destiny?

271
00:47:15,407 --> 00:47:16,949
When will we ever...

272
00:47:17,700 --> 00:47:19,494
be free?

273
00:47:22,539 --> 00:47:24,290
Not until the day we die?

274
00:47:40,847 --> 00:47:44,184
Ok Soo... Concubine Li...
Your Highness, please calm down.

275
00:47:44,475 --> 00:47:45,644
Don't forget

276
00:47:46,477 --> 00:47:47,854
your own mission.

277
00:47:48,271 --> 00:47:49,981
You must live for the sake
of your people.

278
00:47:50,315 --> 00:47:52,692
Only with life is there hope.

279
00:47:54,402 --> 00:47:55,653
Promise me,

280
00:47:56,154 --> 00:47:57,530
you will live!

281
00:47:59,657 --> 00:48:02,284
You would have me live
in such agony?

282
00:48:05,913 --> 00:48:07,081
Very well.

283
00:48:08,165 --> 00:48:10,875
Very well. I promise you.

284
00:48:15,297 --> 00:48:17,173
I'll live for you.

285
00:50:28,506 --> 00:50:29,757
You! Freeze!

286
00:55:06,644 --> 00:55:07,895
I'm levitating!

287
00:55:31,585 --> 00:55:33,128
Mid-air coffee.

288
00:55:42,220 --> 00:55:43,138
Maggie!

289
00:55:44,264 --> 00:55:45,681
Don't!

290
00:55:54,231 --> 00:55:55,149
Hello?

291
00:55:55,816 --> 00:55:58,152
Jack. Our project has succeeded.

292
00:56:00,112 --> 00:56:01,363
Well, almost!

293
00:56:01,738 --> 00:56:03,698
What? It's a meteorite?

294
00:56:05,159 --> 00:56:08,202
- Outside our solar system?
- <i>That's right.</i>

295
00:56:08,453 --> 00:56:10,539
<i>We must now find the rest of them.</i>

296
00:56:11,581 --> 00:56:13,166
<i>Where's the painting from the coffin?</i>

297
00:56:13,457 --> 00:56:14,584
It's here with me.

298
00:56:15,168 --> 00:56:17,170
I'm going to Xian. Meet me there.

299
00:56:18,421 --> 00:56:19,713
Bring the painting with you.

300
00:56:20,006 --> 00:56:21,424
<i>- Okay.</i>
- Good. See you soon.

301
00:56:25,553 --> 00:56:26,804
I'm coming with you.

302
00:57:00,627 --> 00:57:05,591
I believe it was forged
some time during the Qin dynasty,

303
00:57:07,718 --> 00:57:09,470
This type of scale-like surface material

304
00:57:09,761 --> 00:57:12,013
is found only in Qin-dynasty artifacts.

305
00:57:12,513 --> 00:57:14,808
Looking at the design and decorations,

306
00:57:16,059 --> 00:57:18,769
I'd say it belonged to a Qin general.

307
00:57:19,479 --> 00:57:20,896
This is a national treasure.

308
00:57:23,483 --> 00:57:24,609
Be careful.

309
00:57:28,738 --> 00:57:30,740
Wait. What are you doing?

310
00:57:30,906 --> 00:57:32,199
The sword is ours!

311
00:57:32,491 --> 00:57:34,784
Jack has bequeathed it to our museum.

312
00:57:38,288 --> 00:57:40,957
Our foundation financed this project.

313
00:57:41,541 --> 00:57:43,502
Anything found
should belong to the foundation.

314
00:57:43,668 --> 00:57:45,420
How can you donate the sword
to the museum?

315
00:57:45,629 --> 00:57:49,132
The sword's a grade one national relic.
It belongs to all of humanity.

316
00:57:49,423 --> 00:57:52,802
It's only right we return it to a museum
where it can be seeing by everybody.

317
00:57:52,927 --> 00:57:55,888
Anyway, what's key to the project
are the meteorites.

318
00:57:56,097 --> 00:57:58,266
These two artifacts
have nothing to do with them.

319
00:57:58,807 --> 00:58:00,809
Before my experiments
draw a conclusion,

320
00:58:01,143 --> 00:58:02,936
anything may prove
to be a critical link.

321
00:58:03,103 --> 00:58:05,022
