is precisely the future!

325
00:58:13,989 --> 00:58:15,407
Fine, if that's what you say,

326
00:58:15,532 --> 00:58:17,742
then how come these
2,000 year-old artifacts

327
00:58:17,909 --> 00:58:19,243
are so important to you?

328
00:58:19,327 --> 00:58:21,203
I risked my life for that sword!

329
00:58:21,288 --> 00:58:22,372
That was me.

330
00:58:27,168 --> 00:58:29,711
Okay! In that case,
when I find the meteorites,

331
00:58:29,837 --> 00:58:31,839
- you'll still give them away?
- Yes.

332
00:58:33,049 --> 00:58:35,467
As long as it's someone else's artifacts,
I'll return them.

333
00:58:36,260 --> 00:58:38,804
No one can plunder relics
from someone else's country

334
00:58:38,970 --> 00:58:40,472
and put them in their own museums.

335
00:58:40,639 --> 00:58:43,517
They call it "safe-keeping,"
but it's theft.

336
00:58:43,642 --> 00:58:44,976
It's despicable behavior.

337
00:58:48,104 --> 00:58:49,647
So, what are we going to do now?

338
00:58:51,816 --> 00:58:52,900
What can I do?

339
00:59:01,867 --> 00:59:02,743
William.

340
00:59:03,953 --> 00:59:06,789
Do you want to meet your sponsor
for these last ten years?

341
00:59:07,873 --> 00:59:10,292
Of course.
But he doesn't want to see me.

342
00:59:10,918 --> 00:59:12,336
I'll bring you to him now.

343
00:59:13,378 --> 00:59:15,088
- Right now?
- Come with me.

344
00:59:21,720 --> 00:59:25,098
I'll return these relics
to Dasar for you.

345
00:59:27,100 --> 00:59:28,059
Thank you.

346
00:59:46,576 --> 00:59:47,660
Professor Koo?

347
00:59:48,286 --> 00:59:49,454
It's you?

348
00:59:49,954 --> 00:59:51,956
It's been years since I was a professor.

349
01:00:01,674 --> 01:00:04,510
Mr. Koo, you've been
funding my work

350
01:00:04,760 --> 01:00:06,637
all these years?

351
01:00:07,013 --> 01:00:07,888
That's right.

352
01:00:08,305 --> 01:00:11,099
I had my eye on you
even before you graduated.

353
01:00:12,934 --> 01:00:15,896
Maggie, cancel my contract
with the foundation.

354
01:00:16,730 --> 01:00:20,108
I won't accept sponsorship
from a tomb-raiding "archaeologist."

355
01:00:24,070 --> 01:00:28,533
And you and Jack
weren't raiding tombs in Dasar?

356
01:00:32,870 --> 01:00:36,123
I've unearthed many treasures
in my lifetime.

357
01:00:37,332 --> 01:00:41,711
But the best ones I found
are you and Jack.

358
01:00:43,422 --> 01:00:45,257
- Don't you hate him?
- No.

359
01:00:47,967 --> 01:00:49,678
Even if he has hurt me deeply.

360
01:00:55,684 --> 01:00:57,101
So what do you want from me?

361
01:00:59,896 --> 01:01:01,355
Stay with Jack.

362
01:01:02,731 --> 01:01:03,942
Follow him.

363
01:01:05,151 --> 01:01:06,319
Enlighten him.

364
01:01:07,611 --> 01:01:10,989
He'll make you
the world's greatest scientist.

365
01:01:12,491 --> 01:01:14,326
Isn't that your life's dream?

366
01:01:20,498 --> 01:01:23,793
"The 36th year of the emperor's reign.

367
01:01:24,002 --> 01:01:27,339
A star fell on the eastern province,
and turned to stone on Earth."

368
01:01:27,505 --> 01:01:28,881
{\an8}RECORDS OF THE GRAND HISTORIAN

369
01:01:29,048 --> 01:01:31,175
{\an8}"The meteorite was engraved..."

370
01:01:31,843 --> 01:01:34,095
"...<i>with a curse on the emperor.</i>

371
01:01:34,386 --> 01:01:38,682
<i>So the emperor tried to kill everyone
around him...</i>

372
01:01:39,183 --> 01:01:44,480
